{
  "doc_id": "27735",
  "text": "The equilibrium concentrations and activity coefficients were obtained by solving an e-NRTL based vapor-liquid equilibrium model which accounts for the liquid non-idealities [CITATION_1] . When using concentration based kinetic model, the concentration based equilibrium constants given in eq. (31) were calculated individually for each experiment by setting the bulk liquid reaction rates to zero and using the equilibrium concentrations from the e-NRTL model. This ensures that thermodynamic model is used in a consistent way. Kinetic models developed by Putta et al. [CITATION_2] and used here, have previously been shown to be able to represent experimental mass transfer data over a wide range of temperatures, concentrations, CO2 loadings and CO2 partial pressures.",
